Feedback from *Fitch APAC*:
• The ability to detect more *Paywall Content and APAC Broadcast channels:* Titles include _Nikkei (Japan)_, trade titles under Haymarket e.g. _FinanceAsia, CorporateTreasurer, AsiaInvestor_ etc, as well as _<https://www.theasset.com/|The Asset>_ and _<https://www.caixin.com/?HOLDZH|Caixin>_; Broadcast Channels in Singapore, Japan, Hong Kong etc. They have their own corporate subscription but they want Signal to be able to flag articles they need or have them included in the charts on the platform;
• *Translation*: "RWS has not been doing a good job in getting *Fitc

*Hawthorn Advisors* would like to:
1. Have the possibility to change font size when creating reports;
2. See the authors of the articles being included in article data.

*Need:* FIS APAC would like to be able to:
(1) manually add missing articles to the platform / dashboard;
(2) request to have articles displayed on the platform even if we have only the headline;
(3) full-text articles from the Hong Kong Economic Times.
*Problem:* HKET, which is one of the major newspapers in Hong Kong, has written an article about WorldPay but the article is missed on the platform due to heavy paywall. The client questioned why we wouldn’t be able to detect this article when Worldpay is mentioned in the headline before the content gate. She thinks we should at least let them

Adevinta would like to see:
    ◦ dashboard charts to show date range when downloaded as PNG;
    ◦ ability to select multiple charts and export to powerpoint;
    ◦ see sentiment over time of related organisations within main dashboard;
    ◦ sentiment over time graph to show % of positive/negative coverage (as well as figures)
